What is modinfo?

modinfo = "module info"

It shows detailed information about a kernel module (.ko file)

You can use it to:

Check who made the module
Know what version it is
See the license (GPL, etc.)
Find the file path
View module parameters (settings you can change)

Basic Usage

modinfo <module_name>

Example:

modinfo usb_storage

This might output something like:

vbnet
Copy
Edit
filename:       /lib/modules/6.1.0/kernel/drivers/usb/storage/usb-storage.ko
version:        1.0
license:        GPL
description:    USB Mass Storage driver for Linux
author:         Linux USB Team
depends:        
retpoline:      Y
